    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">III.</span> Scope of Representation</div>

    <p class="clause">
        The Client hereby retains and employs <span class="clause-label">DeliPat Law Group, PLLC</span>
        (hereinafter "the Firm" or "Attorney") to represent Client in connection with a
        personal injury claim arising from the above-described incident. The scope of this
        representation includes, but is not limited to, the following:
    </p>
    <ul class="clause-list">
        <li>Investigation of the facts and circumstances surrounding the incident;</li>
        <li>Gathering and preservation of evidence, including medical records, police reports, photographs, and witness statements;</li>
        <li>Negotiation with insurance companies, defendants, and their representatives on Client's behalf;</li>
        <li>Filing a lawsuit and litigating the matter in the appropriate court, if necessary;</li>
        <li>Representing Client at depositions, mediations, arbitrations, and trial proceedings;</li>
        <li>Handling all appeals, if agreed upon in a separate writing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="clause">
        This Agreement does <b>not</b> cover criminal matters, matters unrelated to the above incident,
        or any separate claims not expressly identified herein. Any expansion of scope requires a
        written amendment signed by both parties.
    </p>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         CONTINGENCY FEE
    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">IV.</span> Attorney's Fees — Contingency</div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <span class="highlight-label">&#9888; Important Fee Notice — Please Read Carefully</span>
        The Firm's fee is contingent upon recovery. <b>If there is no recovery, Client owes no attorney's fees.</b>
        However, Client may still be responsible for certain costs and expenses as described in Section V below.
    </div>

    <p class="clause">
        In consideration for legal services rendered, the Client agrees to pay the Firm a contingency fee
        calculated as a percentage of the <b>gross recovery</b> (total amount recovered before deduction of
        costs and expenses), as follows:
    </p>

    <div class="fee-display">33⅓%</div>
    <div class="fee-caption">Pre-Litigation / Pre-Suit Settlement</div>

    <div class="fee-display" style="font-size:18pt; margin-top:12pt;">40%</div>
    <div class="fee-caption">If Lawsuit is Filed / Trial Proceeds</div>

    <p class="clause" style="margin-top:12pt;">
        The fee percentage shall be applied to the <b>gross recovery</b> before deducting costs.
        If a lawsuit is filed, the applicable percentage increases to the trial rate as stated above.
        In cases involving a minor or an incompetent, the fee is subject to court approval.
        The Firm reserves the right to seek a higher fee upon court application if extraordinary
        circumstances warrant.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        "Recovery" includes all sums obtained for the Client by settlement, judgment, arbitration award,
        or any other means, whether paid in a lump sum or in installments.
    </p>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         COSTS & EXPENSES
    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">V.</span> Costs and Expenses</div>

    <p class="clause">
        In addition to attorney's fees, the Client is responsible for all costs and expenses incurred
        in connection with the representation. These costs will be <b>advanced by the Firm</b> and
        deducted from the Client's share of any recovery. If there is no recovery, the Client's
        obligation for costs is governed by a separate written agreement and may be waived at the
        Firm's sole discretion. Costs may include, but are not limited to:
    </p>
    <ul class="clause-list">
        <li>Filing fees, court costs, and service of process fees;</li>
        <li>Medical records retrieval and expert witness fees;</li>
        <li>Deposition transcripts and court reporter charges;</li>
        <li>Investigation costs, accident reconstruction, and demonstrative evidence;</li>
        <li>Postage, copying, scanning, and reasonable administrative disbursements;</li>
        <li>Travel expenses incurred in connection with the case;</li>
        <li>Mediation and arbitration fees.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="clause">
        The Firm will provide Client with an itemized statement of costs at the conclusion of the
        representation or upon written request. Client authorizes the Firm to incur reasonable and
        necessary costs without prior approval for individual expenditures under <b>$500.00</b>.
        Expenditures exceeding $500.00 will require Client's written or documented verbal consent.
    </p>

