    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">VIII.</span> Settlement Authority and Disbursement of Funds</div>

    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">8.1 Settlement Authority.</span> No settlement shall be made without Client's prior written or
        documented verbal approval. The Firm will present all settlement offers to Client with a recommendation
        and will not accept or reject any offer without Client's express authorization.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">8.2 Trust Account.</span> All settlement proceeds or judgments received on Client's behalf will be
        deposited into the Firm's client trust account (IOLTA) in accordance with applicable state bar rules.
        Disbursement will occur within a reasonable time after funds clear, after deduction of the Firm's
        contingency fee and all outstanding costs.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">8.3 Medical Lien Obligations.</span> Client acknowledges that medical providers, health insurers,
        Medicare, Medicaid, or other lienholders may assert liens against any recovery. The Firm will
        notify Client of all known liens and will use reasonable efforts to negotiate reductions on Client's
        behalf. Client is ultimately responsible for all valid liens.
    </p>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         WITHDRAWAL & TERMINATION
    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">IX.</span> Withdrawal and Termination</div>

    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">9.1 Termination by Client.</span> Client may discharge the Firm at any time upon written notice.
        Upon discharge, Client shall be responsible for the reasonable value of services rendered (quantum meruit)
        and all costs advanced to the date of discharge, regardless of whether a recovery is subsequently obtained.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">9.2 Withdrawal by Firm.</span> The Firm may withdraw from representation in accordance with the
        applicable Rules of Professional Conduct, including, without limitation, situations where the Client
        fails to cooperate, provides false information, or insists on pursuing a course of action the Firm
        believes to be illegal, unethical, or without merit. Upon withdrawal, the Firm is entitled to
        compensation for services rendered to date.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">9.3 File Transfer.</span> Upon termination, the Firm will promptly provide Client with a copy of
        the file. The Firm may retain the original file in accordance with state bar rules.
    </p>

    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         MISCELLANEOUS
    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div class="section-heading"><span class="section-number">X.</span> Additional Provisions</div>

    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.1 No Guarantee of Outcome.</span> The Firm makes no warranty, express or implied,
        regarding the outcome of Client's case. Prior results do not guarantee a similar outcome.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.2 Governing Law.</span> This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the state in which
        the Firm's principal office is located, and any disputes arising hereunder shall be subject to the
        jurisdiction of the courts of that state.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.3 Entire Agreement.</span> This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties
        with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior discussions, representations,
        and agreements. Any modification must be in writing and signed by both parties.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.4 Severability.</span> If any provision of this Agreement is found to be invalid or
        unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.5 Electronic Signatures.</span> The parties agree that electronic signatures obtained
        through a lawful e-signature service shall be deemed original signatures and shall be fully binding
        for all purposes under applicable law, including the Electronic Signatures in Global and National
        Commerce Act (E-SIGN Act) and applicable state uniform electronic transactions laws.
    </p>
    <p class="clause">
        <span class="clause-label">10.6 Dispute Resolution.</span> Any dispute arising under this Agreement that cannot be
        resolved by mutual agreement shall first be submitted to non-binding mediation before a neutral
        mediator agreed upon by the parties. If mediation is unsuccessful, either party may seek relief
        in a court of competent jurisdiction.
    </p>

